headline: Assessing Whether Applied Materials (AMAT) Still Looks Overvalued After Strong Recent Returns
summary: Applied Materials overview after recent performance moves Applied Materials (AMAT) has been on investors’ radar after a period of strong share price performance, with total return figures over the past year and past 3 months drawing attention to its semiconductor exposure. headline: Wealthy Families Are Worried About Geopolitics. But They’re Not Rushing to AI, Crypto, or Gold
summary: A new report from J.P. Morgan Private Bank reveals that family offices around the world are mostly sticking to large-cap equities and alternative assets. Still, some 65% describe AI investments as a future priority.

headline: Super Bowl LX, Coinbase earnings, jobs data & CPI: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime Host Jared Blikre previews several of the biggest stories to come throughout next week, including Super Bowl LX this Sunday; a deluge of earnings from companies like Coinbase Global (COIN), Ford (F), McDonald's (MCD), and Moderna (MRNA); January's delayed jobs report on Wednesday followed by last month's Consumer Price Index (CPI) reading on Friday; and a wave of commentary from Federal Reserve officials. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.
